# .conformance-banned — banned term list for gate_a
#
# Copy this file to .conformance-banned (gitignored) and replace the placeholder
# lines below with the real proprietary terms for your deployment.
#
# Format:
#   - One term per line.
#   - Lines starting with "#" are comments and are ignored.
#   - Blank lines are ignored.
#   - Terms are matched case-insensitively against both file contents and file paths.
#   - Both names (client, vendor, operator) and real ID fragments belong here.
#
# In CI, this file is materialised from the CONFORMANCE_BANNED repository secret
# (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions). gate_a will SKIP (with a warning)
# if .conformance-banned is absent locally, but CI fails hard if the secret is unset.

your-client-name
your-operator-username
your-source-vendor-name
your-sink-vendor-name
your-board-column-id-fragment
your-numeric-board-id
